The Saltglass Reach is a transit corridor between the inland desert and the eastern sea, terminating at the port city of Mafdet. It spans four terrain bands running west to east.

The Mirror Flats are hard salt crust, the evaporation basin of the vanished Iseth Reach river. Blinding by day, reflective by night. Caravans cross at dawn and dusk only.

The Glasswind Belts are fields of wind-cut silica shards created when the Ninth Meridian's thermal pulse fused surface sand into glass. Guide navigation relies on glass color: milky means stable ground, amber warns of thermal faults, violet marks eclipse-rite residue.

The Tariff Cairn Lines are ruined checkpoint chains where cargo once transitioned from inland charter law to maritime levy law. Three parallel routes existed: Swift Line (light high-value cargo), Heavy Road (bulk goods), Sealed Route (funerary and relic consignments under armed escort).

The Tidemouth Dunes mark the coastal approach to Mafdet. The Shoreward Seal boundary stone was the legal threshold between inland and maritime jurisdiction.

The Shoreward Conversion was the formal process translating cargo, contracts, and obligations from desert law to maritime law. Water-debt was discharged by pouring measured volume onto basalt. Specialist Shoreward Assessors used conversion charts called Shoreward Tables, ancestors of Mafdet's modern Saltweight standard.

Key factions: Reach Wardens patrol cairn lines and issue transit seals. Red Sand Outriders (Mafdet's debt-leverage consortium) prey on distressed caravans. Glasswalk Guides are hereditary neutral navigators with chitin-soled shoes who guide anyone who pays. Synod Whisper Cells use the Glasswind Belts as smuggling corridors.

The landscape is entirely artificial. The salt is dead river deposit. The glass is catastrophe residue. The cairns are collapsed legal infrastructure.
