The Saltglass Reach is Mafdet's threshold, not a distant region. Every overland convoy reaching Mafdet's Ledger House counters crossed this corridor on foot. The Shoreward Conversion is Mafdet's process, maintained by Mafdet's Assessors, sworn at Mafdet's Shrine.

The Mirror Flats are Mafdet's outer boundary. Signal towers on the Flats reveal approaching caravans for miles. Mafdet sees them before they see Mafdet. By design.

The Glasswind Belts are both natural defense and deepest scar. The thermal pulse that destroyed the Scorched Wastes fused the sand into brittle glass. Mafdet built on that glass. Every guardian-name sworn at the Shrine acknowledges this origin: Mafdet is the city the disaster made.

The Tariff Cairn Lines fed directly into the Ledger Houses. Three routes — Swift Line, Heavy Road, Sealed Route — each required different attestation. Mafdet's four Ledger Houses descend from those cairn assessors. The Quarantine Ledger descends from the Sealed Route's relic handlers, who classified pyramid-origin artifacts before Mafdet had walls.

The Shoreward Seal at the Tidemouth Dunes is where the Dual-Attestation Protocol takes physical form. Inland provenance verified against charter stamps. Maritime risk assessed against vessel and season. Both must align before the harbor chain drops. No exceptions, no urgency waivers, no rank privileges.

Reach Wardens are Mafdet's first intelligence layer. Disrupted caravans or unattested cargo in the Glasswind Belts trigger raised chains and increased Ledger House inspection thresholds. Glasswalk Guides are neutral — but Mafdet tracks who they guide, when, and from which direction. Red Sand Outriders prey on distressed caravans but recover goods otherwise lost. Their cargo enters under amber-seal protocols. Mafdet pays fairly, including for uncomfortable means of arrival.
